♪ The coffee's black, and it is hot ♪

15:03.028 --> 15:05.864
♪ Forget about everything you're not ♪

15:05.864 --> 15:08.450
♪ Just go somewhere
and avoid your problems ♪

15:08.450 --> 15:11.036
♪ Instead of facing them ♪

15:11.036 --> 15:13.914
♪ Yeah, coffee ♪

15:13.914 --> 15:16.917
♪

15:19.753 --> 15:21.255
♪ theme ends ♪

15:21.255 --> 15:25.050
PINKY: Narfs is filmed in front of
a live studio audience. Narfs!

15:25.050 --> 15:27.219
[audience applause, cheering]

15:27.219 --> 15:29.596
[grunts]
[thunder crashes]

15:29.596 --> 15:32.432
‐ Afternoon, Pinky.
ALL: Brain!

15:32.891 --> 15:35.143
‐ How does everyone in here know my name?

15:35.143 --> 15:37.771
‐ This is a place where
everybody knows your name.

15:37.771 --> 15:39.398
Didn't you listen to the theme song?

15:39.398 --> 15:42.317
‐ It didn't mention that
in the theme song.

15:42.317 --> 15:44.987
[coffee maker whistling]
‐ Oh. Maybe that's that other song

15:44.987 --> 15:47.489
that's almost the same, but way better.

15:47.489 --> 15:51.410
‐ Regardless, it's quite a depressing
ditty for a comedy show, don't you think?

15:51.410 --> 15:54.121
Don't any of you have hopes or dreams?
[coffee maker whistling, rattling]

15:55.122 --> 15:57.875
‐ I hope I can get another coffee!

15:57.875 --> 16:00.836
[audience laughter]

16:00.836 --> 16:04.131
[laughing]
‐ [sighs] Forget it.

16:04.131 --> 16:05.799
[grunts]
[laughter continues]

16:05.799 --> 16:07.634
[whistling, rattling]
‐ [laughing] Ooh?

16:08.594 --> 16:10.596
BRAIN:
Warner Brothers!

16:10.596 --> 16:12.806
‐ It took Warner Brothers eight years

16:12.806 --> 16:15.309
to calm Brain down. [grunts]

16:16.101 --> 16:18.979
And when that didn't work,
they threatened to make him

16:18.979 --> 16:21.440
the "next Urkel."

16:21.440 --> 16:23.775
And with that, he was back the same day

16:23.775 --> 16:26.028
to shoot this next pilot.

16:26.028 --> 16:27.029
[bars and tone]

16:27.029 --> 16:29.990
♪ Fresh Prince of Bel Air‐style music ♪

16:35.245 --> 16:38.749
‐ ♪ So, this is a tale,
I'm telling you how ♪

16:38.749 --> 16:40.834
♪ A mouse's life got all messed around ♪

16:40.834 --> 16:43.253
♪ And I'd rather take no time
and tell you point blank ♪

16:43.253 --> 16:46.048
♪ About how I became
the Fresh Pinky of Burbank ♪

16:47.716 --> 16:50.802
♪ Narf! Narf Narf! Narf! Poit! ♪

16:50.802 --> 16:53.889
♪

16:53.889 --> 16:55.265
[grunts]

16:56.016 --> 16:57.518
[audience cheering]

16:58.060 --> 17:01.563
‐ Pinky! You were supposed
to be back over an hour ago!

17:01.563 --> 17:04.399
‐ My bad, Brain.
I guess I'm not used to the rules

17:04.399 --> 17:06.902
because I'm from
the wrong side of the tracks.

17:07.903 --> 17:11.823
‐ Well, be that as it may,
you're going to have a lot

17:11.823 --> 17:14.785
of explaining to do
when Mom and Dad get home.

17:14.785 --> 17:17.496
‐ Why would I have to explain
that I was late? [grunts]

17:17.496 --> 17:19.998
They'll never know, unless you tell 'em.

17:19.998 --> 17:22.000
AUDIENCE:
Ooh...

17:22.000 --> 17:24.962
‐ Are you suggesting that I lie

17:24.962 --> 17:26.797
to my mother and father?

17:27.256 --> 17:30.676
‐ All I'm saying is what they
don't know can't hurt them.

17:30.676 --> 17:32.594
[audience cheering]

17:32.594 --> 17:36.473
‐ Wow, Pinky.
I suppose despite my academic prowess,

17:36.473 --> 17:39.017
I still can learn quite a bit from you.

17:39.017 --> 17:41.603
‐ You're darn right, Brain.
You've got the book smarts,

17:41.603 --> 17:43.856
but I've got the street smarts.

17:43.856 --> 17:46.775
‐ I've got street smarts, too! Heck,

17:46.775 --> 17:50.112
I've even got street moves! Check it out!

17:50.112 --> 17:53.615
[audience cheering]
♪ hip hop music playing ♪

17:53.615 --> 17:56.159
[cheering continues]

17:56.159 --> 17:59.746
They love me. They really, really love me!

18:00.205 --> 18:02.624
♪

18:02.624 --> 18:06.336
‐ Huzzah! What is the word, my good man?

18:06.336 --> 18:09.464
[laughs]
[crowd cheering]

18:09.464 --> 18:10.799
[laughing]

18:10.799 --> 18:12.134
[Egwind grunts]

18:12.759 --> 18:15.220
[crickets chirping]

18:15.220 --> 18:17.681
[crowd cheering]
[grunts]

18:17.681 --> 18:20.475
[audience gasps]
‐ You philistines.

18:20.475 --> 18:22.603
I've debased myself in front of you

18:22.603 --> 18:24.521
with my circus chicanery,

18:24.521 --> 18:29.484
and yet, you worship at the feet of
this sunglassed buffoon!

18:29.484 --> 18:33.030
AUDIENCE MEMBER: Woo!
‐ Well, I will be your Pagliacci no more!

18:33.030 --> 18:34.072
[Egwind gasps]

18:34.072 --> 18:36.200
‐ Fare thee well!

18:36.200 --> 18:37.326
[crash]

18:37.326 --> 18:39.703
‐ Good riddance, you third rate,

18:39.703 --> 18:41.955
third wheel ham actor!

18:41.955 --> 18:43.624
[eagle screeches]
[Egwind screams]

18:43.624 --> 18:45.334
♪

18:46.668 --> 18:50.422
I am finished doing
terrible sitcom pilots!

18:50.422 --> 18:52.257
There's more to life than being told

18:52.257 --> 18:54.593
what to say and do all the time, Pinky!

18:54.593 --> 18:57.179
Now, come with me!
‐ Righto!

18:57.179 --> 18:59.473
‐ We must prepare for tomorrow night.

18:59.473 --> 19:01.683
‐ Why, Brain? What are
we gonna do tomorrow night?

19:01.683 --> 19:04.811
‐ Try to take over the world!

19:04.811 --> 19:07.606
‐ And with that iconic proclamation,

19:07.606 --> 19:12.319
the highly successful
Pinky and the Brain franchise was born.

19:12.319 --> 19:14.696
And now, it's dead

19:14.696 --> 19:16.532
because they're missing.

19:16.532 --> 19:18.200
[phone rings]

19:18.200 --> 19:19.826
What is it!?

19:19.826 --> 19:22.287
Oh! You found them!

19:22.287 --> 19:25.707
Wonderful. Get them back on set!

19:25.707 --> 19:28.126
[grunts]
‐ How adorable.

19:28.126 --> 19:31.713
She thinks she's punishing us,
when she's actually punishing

19:31.713 --> 19:34.049
our clones.
‐ Clones?

19:34.049 --> 19:35.217
‐ That's right.

19:36.176 --> 19:39.179
♪

19:39.429 --> 19:40.722
[alarm blares]

19:44.768 --> 19:48.689
After receiving the latest script
of our "adventures,"

19:48.689 --> 19:50.607
I reached my breaking point.

19:50.607 --> 19:53.777
I will no longer do the bidding
of my television overlords.

19:54.695 --> 19:55.654
Instead,

19:55.654 --> 19:58.532
I have created clones
who will do my bidding,

19:58.532 --> 20:01.785
leaving us free to truly
pursue world domination.

20:02.744 --> 20:06.540
‐ So, you mean to tell me
the Pinky and the Brain show

20:06.540 --> 20:08.125
isn't going to be us anymore?

20:08.125 --> 20:11.128
‐ Precisely. No one will be the wiser

20:11.128 --> 20:13.672
as these clones are indistinguishable

20:13.672 --> 20:15.465
from us in every facet!

20:15.465 --> 20:18.468
‐ [Brain's voice]: Gee, Brain.
What do you wanna do tonight?

20:18.468 --> 20:19.970
‐ [Pinky's voice]: Pancakes!

20:19.970 --> 20:22.890
‐ Narf... [inhales deeply]

20:22.890 --> 20:25.642
‐ Egad! It's like looking in the mirror!

20:25.642 --> 20:26.935
[sighs]

20:26.935 --> 20:29.563
‐ Cloning is an art, not a science.

20:29.563 --> 20:33.192
And alas, I am merely
the world's foremost scientific mind.

20:34.151 --> 20:37.321
Come, Pinky.
We must prepare for tomorrow night.

20:37.321 --> 20:39.740
‐ Why, Brain?
What are we gonna do tomorrow night?

20:39.740 --> 20:42.492
[gasps] Ooh, please let it be pancakes!

20:42.492 --> 20:43.744
[machine hissing]

20:43.744 --> 20:46.455
‐ The same thing we do every night, Pinky.

20:46.455 --> 20:48.415
Try to take over the world!

20:48.415 --> 20:50.417
[hissing, rattling]

20:51.502 --> 20:53.629
♪

20:57.382 --> 20:59.009
[VCR clicking, whirring]

20:59.009 --> 21:01.887
♪ distorted music ♪

21:01.887 --> 21:04.890
♪ retro upbeat music ♪

21:07.351 --> 21:10.395
‐ Hey, gang!
It's time for Everyday Safety!

21:10.395 --> 21:12.105
‐ That's right! We're here to give you

21:12.105 --> 21:15.192
everyday safety tips for
the most common emergencies.

21:15.192 --> 21:16.818
‐ Tonight, what to do in the event of

21:16.818 --> 21:20.239
a giant, exploding syrup factory
at the top of a very tall hill

21:20.239 --> 21:21.532
overlooking your city.

21:21.532 --> 21:23.534
♪

21:25.786 --> 21:27.538
Think fast! Don't panic!

21:27.538 --> 21:30.499
A million gallons of piping hot syrup
are racing toward you!

21:30.499 --> 21:32.584
First,
grab your emergency supplies.

21:32.584 --> 21:35.546
They should be in your
Exploding Syrup Factory Emergency Bag.

21:35.546 --> 21:38.048
‐ It should contain an inflatable raft,

21:38.048 --> 21:39.925
a metric ton of ice,

21:39.925 --> 21:41.677
an ant farm with three active queens,

21:41.677 --> 21:43.637
some pancake mix, a bat,

21:43.637 --> 21:45.097
and a radio.

21:49.434 --> 21:51.854
‐ Inflate the raft and throw it
at the syrup wave

21:51.854 --> 21:53.939
to buy yourself some time.
[grunts]

21:57.442 --> 21:59.486
YAKKO:
Now, carve the metric ton of ice

21:59.486 --> 22:02.239
into an authentic igloo
and take shelter inside.

22:02.239 --> 22:05.117
‐ Better get carving!
That syrup's coming in hot!

22:05.117 --> 22:06.577
♪

22:06.577 --> 22:08.579
[grinding]
‐ It's finished!

22:09.538 --> 22:10.539
[door slams]

22:14.543 --> 22:16.044
♪ relaxed music ♪

22:17.129 --> 22:18.547
[rattling]

22:20.007 --> 22:23.510
‐ Oh no! My hands are sticky,
and I don't have a napkin

22:23.510 --> 22:25.596
because it's an emergency.

22:25.596 --> 22:27.890
‐ Don't worry.
That's what the ants are for.

22:27.890 --> 22:28.974
♪

22:30.601 --> 22:32.352
[ants chirping]

22:32.352 --> 22:33.353
[gasps]

22:33.353 --> 22:34.479
‐ What's the radio for?

22:34.479 --> 22:36.773
‐ Once the syrup cools,
we'll be trapped in here

22:36.773 --> 22:39.443
for millions of years
like mosquitoes in amber,

22:39.443 --> 22:41.236
so we'll need some entertainment.

22:42.446 --> 22:45.949
NPR DJ:
You're listening to hour 97

22:45.949 --> 22:48.952
of "The Art and Craft of Storytelling,"

22:48.952 --> 22:50.495
with Irv Gold.

22:50.495 --> 22:52.998
IRV GOLD:
I often ask myself, what is storytell‐‐

22:52.998 --> 22:54.166
[Dot grunts]
[fizzling]

22:54.166 --> 22:56.502
‐ And that is what the bat's for.

22:56.502 --> 22:58.253
This has been Everyday Safety.

22:58.253 --> 23:00.255
Tune in next time
when we share tips

23:00.255 --> 23:02.466
for when you're with your grandmother
visiting a home

23:02.466 --> 23:05.302
for rehabilitated rattlesnakes,
and there's a power failure

23:05.302 --> 23:07.679
that opens the doors to
the rattlesnake enclosure,

23:07.679 --> 23:09.765
but also your pockets
are filled with maracas,

23:09.765 --> 23:11.892
so you can't tell where
the sounds are coming from.

23:11.892 --> 23:13.352
[hissing, rattling]

23:13.352 --> 23:15.354
‐ Who wants the first Flatty Patty?

23:15.354 --> 23:18.190
‐ Mm! Oh no! We forgot the butter!

23:18.190 --> 23:19.733
Don't worry, I'll go get some.

23:19.733 --> 23:20.776
DOT/YAKKO:
No!

23:20.776 --> 23:22.277
[splattering]
[gasps]

23:22.277 --> 23:23.612
♪

23:23.612 --> 23:25.906
WAKKO [distorted]:
Oh, the viscosity!

23:26.573 --> 23:28.784
♪ retro upbeat music ♪

23:30.786 --> 23:33.789
♪
